Pynguin is a python-based turtle graphics application.
    It combines an editor, interactive interpreter, and
    graphics display area.

It is meant to be an easy environment for introducing
    some programming concepts to beginning programmers.


http://pynguin.googlecode.com/


This release fixes the problem loading saved files in Windows.


Pynguin is tested with Python 3.3.1 and PyQt 4.10 and
    now requires QsciScintilla (tested with version 2.7.1)

Pynguin is released under GPLv3.


Changes in pynguin-0.16:
    Important fixes
        - Fixes loading saved files in Windows
        - Ensures that prompt is visible after SyntaxError in console

    Other fixes

    Pynguin API

    Canvas

    UI

    Integrated Editor

    Integrated Console
        - Delays check for prompt slightly to ensure that prompt is visible
            - SyntaxError would sometimes leave console in a bad state

